 A+B+C= 180^\circ
\cot(D) =  \cot(A)+ \cot(B) + \cot(C)
\sin(A-D)\sin(B-D)\sin(C-D)=[\sin(D)]^3
\cot(D) =  \cot(A)+ \cot(B) + \cot(C)
 A+B+C= 180^\circ
\sin(A+B)=\sin(180^\circ-C)=\sin C
\sin(B+C)=\sin(180^\circ-A)=\sin A
\sin(A+C)=\sin(180^\circ-B)=\sin B
\cot D-\cot A=\cot B+\cot C
\implies\frac{\sin(A-D)}{\sin D\sin A}=\frac{\sin(B+C)}{\sin B\sin C}
